The issue with your code is that you are trying to access the cell value before the iteration has completed. You need to wait until the iteration is finished before accessing the cell value. To do this, you can use the `Iterator.next()` method to move to the next iteration and then access the cell value.

Here's the modified code using `Iterator.next()`:
```java
Iterator<Row> rowIterator = insheet.iterator();
while (rowIterator.hasNext()) {
    Row row = rowIterator.next();
    int column = 2; // the column number
    while (row.getCell(column) != null) {
        System.out.println("Cell value B" + (row.getRowNum() - 1) + ": " + row.getCell(column));
        rowIterator.next(); // move to the next row
    }
}
```
This code uses an iterator to iterate over the rows in the sheet, and then iterates over the cells in each row until it reaches the end of the column. By using `Iterator.next()` to move to the next row after each iteration, you can avoid the null pointer exception.
